TEXT(&beginproblem);

$a = random(2,6,1);
$b = $a + random(1,3,1);

$ans = ($a*$b)/($b-$a);

&ANS(num_cmp($ans));


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Find \(n\) such that \(1 + \frac{i^{(n)}}{n} = (1 + \frac{i^{($a)}}{$a}) / (1 + \frac{i^{($b)}}{$b}) \) where \(i^{($a)}\), \(i^{($b)}\), \(i^{(n)}\)  all produce the same effective rate of interest.


$BR
\(n\) = \{ans_rule(20)\}
EOT


